# CSS Borders

Borders define the outline around elements.

## Basic Border

```css
div {
    border: 2px solid black;
}
```

## Dashed Border

```css
div {
    border: 2px dashed blue;
}
```

## Dotted Border

```css
div {
    border: 2px dotted red;
}
```

## Rounded Corners

```css
div {
    border-radius: 10px;
}
```

## Real-World Example

Cards and buttons often use rounded borders.

## Summary

Borders help separate and highlight content.
